Canada and Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance, have delivered 200,000 doses of mpox vaccine to the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) to support its response to the ongoing outbreak. These doses, distributed under the Access and Allocation Mechanism (AAM), contribute to over 1.2 million mpox vaccines facilitated by Gavi. The DRC remains the epicenter of the epidemic, with over 19,800 cases across 21 African nations. Canadian and Congolese officials emphasized the importance of global solidarity in controlling the outbreak. Gavi continues to secure vaccine access and funding for in-country distribution to contain the health emergency.
